## 4. Disaster Recovery, Volume Snapshots, & Platform Backups
To guarantee protection against sudden platform failures, data corruption events, or localized cluster crashes, the DaaS storage tier enforces an automated backup recovery protocol.

[ Primary Cluster Site ]                           [ Remote DR Site: Wichita ]
+---------------------+                           +-------------------------+

| Jenkins Master PV   |                           |                         |
| (Active Live Storage) |                           |                         |
+----------+----------+                           +------------+------------+

           |                                                   ^
           | (Local Trident Volume Snapshot)                   |
           v                                                   |
+---------------------+                                       |

| Point-in-Time       |=======================================+
| Volume Snapshot     |       (Nightly SnapMirror Replication)
+---------------------+


* Trident-Powered Snapshots: Storage volume states are safely retained utilizing the native volume snapshot framework supported by Astra Trident (available on Trident release versions 20.01 and above running on Kubernetes cluster versions 1.17+).
* Volume Cloning: These point-in-time storage state snapshots capture live data mounted to your Persistent Volumes (PVs) and can be used to instantly clone identical, independent environments for rapid recovery.
* Nightly Remote Disaster Recovery (DR): Snapshots are not retained solely on the local hardware cluster. Every night, automated background jobs run a data replication process (SnapMirror) that transfers snapshots to a geographically isolated remote disaster recovery facility located in Wichita.
* Proactive Infrastructure Alerting: The Enterprise Control Operations (ECO) infrastructure monitoring team maintains real-time alerts linked directly to replication health. If a network disruption occurs or a SnapMirror backup stream fails, the ECO group receives an immediate alert to triage and restore replication parity.

