## 7. Platform Engineering Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)## Q: What actions occur automatically after I commit code and merge a PR?
A: Once code changes are merged into your release branch inside Bitbucket, a web hook hooks back to your CI engine to trigger a release build automatically. The pipeline compiles your source tree, assembles a new container artifact, tags it with the explicit build version number, and deploys it directly to your Dev Namespace.
## Q: Where are final container image tags stored?
A: All freshly generated container images are pushed and securely archived inside your Elastic Container Registry (ECR) image workspace repository.
